'''芬斯伯里圆环'''（Finsbury Circus）是位于[[英国|英国]][[英格兰|英格兰]][[伦敦城|伦敦城]]科尔曼街区（Coleman Street Ward）的公园，占地2.2公顷，是伦敦市边界内最大的公共开放空间<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.visitthecity.co.uk/index.php/attractions/view/177/ |title=Visit the City |access-date=2020-12-30 |archive-date=2012-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120422232153/http://www.visitthecity.co.uk/index.php/attractions/view/177 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。其与伦敦城以北的芬斯伯里广场（Finsbury Square）、几英里外的芬斯伯里公园（Finsbury Park）不同。

==历史==
芬斯伯里圆环创建于1812年，位于下摩尔菲尔德地区，原本屬於芬斯伯里庄园，此莊園早在12世纪就已存在，<ref>'Religious Houses: Houses of Augustinian canonesses', in A History of the County of Middlesex: Volume 1, Physique, Archaeology, Domesday, Ecclesiastical Organization, the Jews, Religious Houses, Education of Working Classes To 1870, Private Education From Sixteenth Century, ed. J S Cockburn, H P F King and K G T McDonnell (London, 1969), pp. 170-182. British History Online http://www.british-history.ac.uk/vch/middx/vol1/pp170-182 {{Wayback|url=http://www.british-history.ac.uk/vch/middx/vol1/pp170-182 |date=20210228164943 }} [accessed 15 October 2020].</ref>第二个贝斯莱姆皇家医院自1675年以来设于此处<ref>Henry Benjamin Wheatley and Peter Cunningham, ''London, Past and Present: its history, associations, and traditions'', II:42, ''s.v.'' "Finsbury Circus".</ref>。圆环之名表明空间呈椭圆形，类似于古罗马[[馬克西穆斯競技場|馬克西穆斯競技場]]，有东西向的长轴。 

原来房屋的最后一栋於1921年拆除。花园以[[椴树|椴树]]为特色，由威廉·蒙塔格根据建筑师小乔治唐斯1815年的设计开发。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.londongardensonline.org.uk/gardens-online-record.asp?ID=COL027 |title=London Gardens Online |access-date=2020-12-30 |archive-date=2018-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802162840/http://www.londongardensonline.org.uk/gardens-online-record.asp?ID=COL027 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 1819年，<ref>James Elmes, ''A Topographical Dictionary of London and its Environs'', 1831, ''s.v.'' "Finsbury Circus".</ref> [[伦敦大学|伦敦学院]]搬进了威廉·布鲁克斯<ref>William Brooks (1786–1867), a pupil of D. R. Roper, a zealous Nonconformist and anti-Papist and a passionate advocate for the abolition of slavery, retired from practice at an early date; he was the father of C.W. Shirley Brooks, well known as the editor of ''Punch'' (Colvin 1995).</ref>在花园北端精心设计的优雅场所<ref>The phrase is Howard Colvin's, in ''A Biographical Dictionary of British Architects 1600-1840'', 3rd edn 1995, ''s.v.'' "Brooks William".</ref>。它于1912年关闭，这些建筑由[[伦敦大学|伦敦大学]]使用，直到1936年拆除。从19世纪20年代开始，圆环的正面是巨大的[[一位论派|一位论派]]教堂，在威廉·约翰逊·福克斯的领导下建造，後來成爲康威大厅伦理协会<ref>{{cite web |title=The building of South Place Chapel, 1821 - Conway Hall |url=https://conwayhall.org.uk/the-building-of-south-place-chapel-1821/ |website=Conway Hall |access-date=2018-08-02 |date=2013-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802162532/https://conwayhall.org.uk/the-building-of-south-place-chapel-1821/ |archive-date=2018-08-02}}</ref>。

[[File:Greenery_in_the_City_-_geograph.org.uk_-_221683.jpg|thumb]]的Britannic House]]
圆环在20世纪初作为公园开放<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.audit-commission.gov.uk/SiteCollectionDocuments/InspectionOutput/InspectionReports/2001/CorpLondon03.pdf |title=Best Value Inspection: Corporation of London Open Spaces Department |date=September 2001 |publisher=Audit Commission |access-date=2010-12-10 |archive-date=2012-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121007223427/http://www.audit-commission.gov.uk/SiteCollectionDocuments/InspectionOutput/InspectionReports/2001/CorpLondon03.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。此前花园是私人空间，由周围建筑物的持有人或租赁者使用。他们反对强制购买，担心公众使用花园会造成滋扰，降低其财产的价值。<ref name="times-1900-03-28">{{cite news |title=City of London (Various Powers) Bill |date=1900-03-28 |work=[[The_Times|The Times]] |page=2, col F |location=London}}</ref>使其成为公共空间的运动由法林登区市政官、[[倫敦市法團|倫敦市法團]]街道委员会成员阿尔菲斯·莫顿领导，<ref name="times-1900-03-28" /><ref name="times-memorial-service">{{cite news |title = Memorial Service. Sir A.C. Morton |date = 1923-05-02 |work = The Times |page = 17, col D |location = London}}</ref>[[倫敦市法團|倫敦市法團]]称圆环为莫顿公园<ref name="times-1919-mulberry">{{cite news |title=News in Brief |date=1919-08-20 |work=The Times |page=7, col F |location=London}}</ref>。 

在椭圆形的西北象限前，矗立着[[埃德溫·魯琴斯|埃德溫·魯琴斯]]的庞大的Britannic House（1921－1925年，列为二级），为[[英伊石油公司|英伊石油公司]]设计，即[[BP|BP]]的前身；其建筑雕塑是弗朗西斯·德温特·伍德的作品。<ref>Philip Ward-Jackson, ''Public Sculpture of the City of London'' 2003:109f.</ref> 它位于最后剩下的原始建筑的遗址上。现在是国际律师事务所史蒂芬生·哈伍德<ref>Harold Philip Clunn, ''London Rebuilt, 1897-1927: an attempt to depict the principal'', 1927:17ff.</ref>。
